globs: *.ts,*.js,*.tsx,*.jsx,*.mts,*.cjs,*.mjs,*.cts
alwaysApply: false
---

Let code breathe — format for human scan, not minification.

## Whitespace

- Newline before `return` in multi-line functions
- Newline before `if`, `for`, `while`, or `switch` unless it opens the function body
- Blank line between logical sections

## Structure

- Match the file you're in: naming, imports, error shapes, abstractions
- Small named helpers over long inline blocks
- Reuse existing helpers before writing new ones
- Shortest diff that fixes the root cause — grep callers, fix shared code once

## Comments

- JSDoc only when behavior isn't obvious from names and types
- `biome-ignore` only with a one-line why
- Intentional shortcuts: `ponytail:` comment naming the ceiling and upgrade path

## TypeScript

- Explicit types on exports and public boundaries; infer locals
- `as const` for literal unions the SDK needs
- `biome-ignore` + justification when `any` is unavoidable (generated SDK generics)

## Tests

- Non-trivial logic → one small `bun:test` file; no fixtures or extra frameworks
- Skip tests for trivial one-liners
